{"priority": "major", "kind": "enhancement", "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/drcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/drcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{247b5408-ae91-4e3c-b2f9-a21994658d11}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "drcsim", "full_name": "osrf/drcsim", "uuid": "{247b5408-ae91-4e3c-b2f9-a21994658d11}"}, "links": {"attachments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/drcsim/issues/88/attachments_page=1.json"}, "self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/drcsim/issues/88.json"}, "watch": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/drcsim/issues/88/watch"}, "comments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/drcsim/issues/88/comments_page=1.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/drcsim/issues/88/infer-ros-distro-from-environment-during"}, "vote": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/drcsim/issues/88/vote"}}, "reporter": {"display_name": "Brian Gerkey", "uuid": "{3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9/5fa9ec73-0fec-4860-a202-e34ae23b6a12/128"}}, "nickname": "Brian Gerkey", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9"}, "title": "Infer ROS distro from environment during configure", "component": null, "votes": 0, "watches": 0, "content": {"raw": "Currently we set `ROS_DISTRO` manually in `CMakeLists.txt`.  That value ends up in the installed `setup.sh`.  We should be able to infer the distro from the environment during configure (because the user must have source a ROS setup file).\r\n\r\nWe were just tripped up by this because were compiling against Groovy but hadn't changed the `ROS_DISTRO` setting.\r\n\r\nThe same thing should be addressed in `sandia_hand` and `osrf_msgs`.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Currently we set <code>ROS_DISTRO</code> manually in <code>CMakeLists.txt</code>.  That value ends up in the installed <code>setup.sh</code>.  We should be able to infer the distro from the environment during configure (because the user must have source a ROS setup file).</p>\n<p>We were just tripped up by this because were compiling against Groovy but hadn't changed the <code>ROS_DISTRO</code> setting.</p>\n<p>The same thing should be addressed in <code>sandia_hand</code> and <code>osrf_msgs</code>.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": {"display_name": "Brian Gerkey", "uuid": "{3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9/5fa9ec73-0fec-4860-a202-e34ae23b6a12/128"}}, "nickname": "Brian Gerkey", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9"}, "state": "resolved", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2013-01-23T04:06:06.123552+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2013-01-25T18:37:08.914948+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 88}